The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Winning streak

 P.C. Sorcar (Jr) and Buddhadev Guha at the Sreeleathers Lucky Draw. Picture by Rashbehari Das

What: Sreeleathers Lucky Draw. 

 Where: Sreeleathers store on Free School Street.

 When: Wednesday morning.

 Take a look: Starting in July, all customers at Sreeleathers were gifted a coupon with every purchase of Rs 699 and above. On Wednesday morning, the contest finale saw the names of 280 lucky winners being drawn from approximately 1,20,000 coupons. 

 Actress Madhabi Mukherjee, writer Buddhadev Guha and magician P.C Sorcar (Jr) were present at the store to pick the winners.

 The winner of the first prize Sandip Chatterjee from Murshidabad bagged silver equal to his body weight. Kapildev Passi and Dhiren Shasmal came in second and drove away Maruti Alto cars. The rest won consolation prizes of Sreeleathers shoes and products worth Rs 1,599 every year for the next 10 years.

 Ten names from each of the 27 nation-wide outlets were drawn from the lottery.




